eir trust.', 74794, 0), (477070, 'I understood it''s a business as far as when you''re drafting someone, and you want a guy you can trust. But there were no questions on my ability or character.', 66880, 0), (477071, 'To bear means to support the weight of that which is held. It is a sacred trust to bear the priesthood, which is the mighty power and authority of God.', 71238, 0), (477072, 'When I went to the prosecutor''s office, I wanted to be one of the good guys that the defense could trust. I''d try fair, clean cases, pull no punches, no below-the-belt stuff. Honorable. Because that''s the kind of prosecutor I wanted to deal with.', 58457, 0), (477073, 'I am a small business owner I''m in the agri-business. That''s about as blind a trust as you can get. We trust in the Lord for rain and many other things. ', 72215, 0), (477074, 'Most teams are naturally flat; they have fewer members than a large enterprise, which allows for intimacy and trust to form. This makes collaborative problem solving in individual teams more straightforward.', 69443, 0), (477075, 'Without trust, the most essential element of innovation - conflict - becomes impossible.', 17487, 0), (477076, 'When a salesperson truly cares about you, trust forms, and you''re more likely to buy, come back for repeat business, and refer new customers.', 14960, 0), (477077, 'I love to see lack of clarity in a performance as well as clarity, as well as trust, as well as the kinds of things that human beings go through. I love to see spontaneity and ''inevitability.'' How it gets there is going to shock the hell out of me, but it will get there somehow.', 68431, 0), (477078, 'In an increasingly polarized world, it''s hard to know whom to trust. CNN will be the only news channel that doesn''t take a side.', 74795, 0), (477079, 'Just because somebody says you are not trustworthy, that doesn''t mean it is so... CNN''s brand equity is built over 37 years doing hard work in very dangerous places... those who rely on