ot stand that whole game of confession, that is: Here I have sinned, now I''m confessing my sins, and describing my path of sin and then in the act of confession I beg for your forgiveness and redemption.', 1327, 0), (477578, 'We only learn at the speed of pain, and we don''t have others in our lives without forgiveness.', 14842, 0), (477579, 'Without forgiveness, there''s no future.', 2109, 0), (477580, 'Humanity is never so beautiful as when praying for forgiveness, or else forgiving another.', 62538, 0), (477581, 'If you look at everything I do - even in ''Boo!'' there''s a message, and it''s always ''faith, family, forgiveness.'' That''s the greatest gift that I''ve been given. I can get a message to the very people I grew up with, the millions who love what I do.', 1776, 0), (477582, 'Many people have trouble with forgiveness because they have been taught it is a singular act to be completed in one sitting. That is not so. Forgiveness has many layers, many seasons.', 625, 0), (477583, 'Beware of the man who does not return your blow: he neither forgives you nor allows you to forgive yourself.', 266, 0), (477584, 'If there is something to pardon in everything, there is also something to condemn.', 11, 0), (477585, 'Every year during their High Holy Days, the Jewish community reminds us all of our need for repentance and forgiveness.', 4008, 0), (477586, 'I have sinned against You, my Lord, and I would ask that your precious blood would wash and cleanse every stain until it is in the seas of God''s forgiveness.', 73512, 0), (477587, 'Things happen for a reason, and the only thing you can do is at night time get on your knees and ask God for forgiveness for anything that you did that you didn''t feel was right.', 67644, 0), (477588, 'One of the secrets of a long and fruitful life is to forgive everybody everything everynight before you go to bed.', 59644, 0), (477589, 'He that cannot forgive others, breaks the bridge over which he himself must pass if he would eve