INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (477751, 'Jealousy can even be good for love. One partner may feel secretly flattered when the other is mildly jealous. And catching someone flirting with your beloved can spark the kind of lust and romance that reignites a relationship.', 52746, 0), (477752, 'More men die of jealousy than of cancer.', 66706, 0), (477753, 'It is not love that is blind, but jealousy.', 6034, 0), (477754, 'Jealousy lives upon doubts. It becomes madness or ceases entirely as soon as we pass from doubt to certainty.', 154, 0), (477755, 'There is never jealousy where there is not strong regard.', 944, 0), (477756, 'Jealousy is the grave of affection.', 5264, 0), (477757, 'Those who are believed to be most abject and humble are usually most ambitious and envious.', 2478, 0), (477758, 'If one of two lovers is loyal, and the other jealous and false, how may their friendship last, for Love is slain!', 9910, 0), (477759, 'Jealousy is, I think, the worst of all faults because it makes a victim of both parties.', 24916, 0), (477760, 'That''s the way I got along in life. I don''t ever remember being particularly jealous of anybody, because I figured if I can''t do it myself, I don''t deserve to get it.', 69955, 0), (477761, 'There''s a constant tension between the excitement of new people and security with one person. If you go with excitement, you create chaos; you hurt people. There''s jealousy, and it gets very messy. If you have security, it can be boring, and you die inside because of all the opportunities missed.', 639, 0), (477762, 'That is ever the way. ''Tis all jealousy to the bride and good wishes to the corpse.', 64116, 0), (477763, 'There is a sort of jealousy which needs very little fire; it is hardly a passion, but a blight bred in the cloudy, damp despondency of uneasy egoism.', 215, 0), (477764, 'A person''s current personality of love, hatred, jealousy, rage or a murderous intent and so on is formed upon genetic elements, education, the environment and a family a person grows in.', 41089, 0), (477765, 'Philosophers see no harm in the Jesuits other than in their effect on humanity and the sciences. The vulgar and especially the prejudiced only hate them from an envy and jealousy born out of conspiracy and intrigue at an organisation which overshadows them.', 3016, 0), (477766, 'Governments are composed of human beings, and all of the frailties that humans possess are absorbed into these governments and become active within these governments. Hatred, anger, jealousy, fear, greed, distrust and the whole host of afflictions that humans must bear, lurk just beneath the surface of civility displayed by ''government.''', 53514, 0), (477767, 'I face so much jealousy, and I am incredibly upset about it.', 70068, 0), (477768, 'It''s a completely useless emotion - jealousy. I don''t go there.', 72831, 0), (477769, 'Rather than writing about international events, I write about individual lives. There is elation and sadness, death and birth, love and jealousy, co-operation and betrayal. All the great emotional transactions that happen wherever people come together.', 54765, 0), (477770, 'Jealousy is a dog''s bark which attracts thieves.', 15784, 0), (477771, 'I don''t get jealousy, I don''t get how people hate each other - I never did.', 66586, 0), (477772, 'Jealousy is the jaundice of the soul.', 8695, 0), (477773, 'Man is jealous because of his amour propre woman is jealous because of her lack of it. ', 1413, 0), (477774, 'A negative judgment gives you more satisfaction than praise, provided it smacks of jealousy.', 8077, 0), (477775, 'We stress humanity, and this is done at considerable cost. We can''t have a lot of dramatics that other shows get away with - promiscuity, greed, jealousy. None of those have a place in ''Star Trek.''', 2599, 0), (477776, 'Jealousy is love bed of burning snarl.', 18119, 0), (477777, 'Innately, there are qualities in human beings that are always repetitive. There are things like love and hate and jealousy that are just going to be there forever.', 74843, 0), (477778, 'The envious die not once, but as oft as the envied win applause.', 1255, 0), (477779, 'Magnanimous people have no vanity, they have no jealousy, and they feed on the true and the solid wherever they find it. And, what is more, they find it everywhere.', 34486, 0), (477780, 'Jealous, adj. Unduly concerned about the preservation of that which can be lost only if not worth keeping.', 224, 0), (477781, 'Jealousy is cruel as the grave: the coals thereof are coals of fire.', 15509, 0), (477782, 'Jealousy is bred in doubts. When those doubts change into certainties, then the passion either ceases or turns absolute madness.', 154, 0), (477783, 'I am drawn to women who are independent and creative, which is problematic because it''s a struggle, a competition of careers. There''s jealousy.', 2519, 0), (477784, 'Anger and jealousy can no more bear to lose sight of their objects than love.', 215, 0), (477785, 'Lovers may be - and indeed generally are - enemies, but they never can be friends, because there must always be a spice of jealousy and a something of Self in all their speculations.', 62558, 0), (477786, 'Back then I didn''t think a woman like that, or a relationship like that, could exist with complete freedom and no jealousy or possessiveness. I thought it sounded too good to be true and I was certainly convinced it wasn''t the life for me!', 48613, 0), (477787, 'I do not say anything from jealousy.', 55096, 0), (477788, 'But when I would see the surrogate, my first instinct, my first reaction would be jealousy, because she was doing what I wanted to do.', 74844, 0), (477789, 'What we used to say was whoever had the bow tie got to lead the band. There was never any jealousy.', 74845, 0), (477790, 'There never was one particle of... jealousy... in the heart of Hyrum Smith.', 56809, 0), (477791, 'If we destroy the biosphere, then mankind will die. We all waste our